  "prompt": "Does Rivers Cuomo have ADHD?",
  "response": "Yes, Rivers Cuomo, the lead vocalist and guitarist of the rock band Weezer, has publicly discussed his experiences with Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD). In various interviews and his memoir, Cuomo has shared insights into how ADHD has influenced his life and creative process. He has mentioned that managing ADHD has been a significant aspect of his personal and professional journey, affecting everything from songwriting to daily routines.\n\nCuomo has also been open about other challenges, such as his struggles with anxiety and obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD), highlighting the importance of mental health awareness and seeking appropriate support. His willingness to speak about these topics has been influential in reducing stigma and encouraging others to address their own mental health needs.\n\nIt's important to note that while Cuomo has shared his personal experiences, discussions about mental health are deeply personal. If you're interested in learning more about his experiences, you might consider reading his memoir, *\"Not Letting Go: My Wild Journey Through Life, Love, and the Pursuit of Weezer.\"* This book provides a more comprehensive look at his life, including his mental health challenges and how they've shaped his career and personal development.\n\nIf you or someone you know is dealing with ADHD or other mental health concerns, it's advisable to consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice and support.",
